<subSubSection id="8DC2EBA2D00271937FCCA2C61D17BC9C" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9C7DC0D1D21FEA6638674A616325DBFD" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="90F49D958B2CDEAE7561E2C8EB153426" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4B3DD769174B7F8F14E9179B7173E9D8" captionStart="Figure 132" captionStartId="F132" captionText="Figure 132. Distribution of Conostegia rubiginosa." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure132" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96490" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">132</figureCitation>
). West coast of Colombia, sea level to 100 m elevation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D3DA179003AB9ADCCCCD28B535559087" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
For the few specimens studied, 
<taxonomicName id="41E9ACB6BCD4C3482BE3DA518113DD1B" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Gleason" authorityYear="1945" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia rubiginosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubiginosa">
<emphasis id="E596E7D52536918E1B7F33806348F41E" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia rubiginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite variable in leaf size and consistency. 
<taxonomicName id="F014D8A44FCF94D54EE25924A31B6C21" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Gleason" authorityYear="1945" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia rubiginosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubiginosa">
<emphasis id="D324ACE598E7B7BFD2B644081914FC6B" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia rubiginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="C318589DE3C64746F57C55F2B3DCCABB" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Markgraf" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia centronioides" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="centronioides">
<emphasis id="7906CE56BA5ABC3A57449B9B38E01D42" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia centronioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CA3A236AE0FB5149F13A2FBA25403DBF" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia lasiopoda" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lasiopoda">
<emphasis id="F4FBD25E3CB34309B73C0A55229F3BF8" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia lasiopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D011FE2B404DA11DEAE09F377E8C8DC8" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia rufescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis id="860E6E9E0ADC109EF22326F70DBDB617" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From 
<taxonomicName id="EF38B81D7C340673503FA5421B86F4BA" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Markgraf" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia centronioides" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="centronioides">
<emphasis id="450B7CAA6240BA6B867CC216CE084196" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia centronioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it can be distinguish by the larger flowers without a constriction in the hypanthium, and denser reddish indument. From 
<taxonomicName id="680313692AC891439306F64424945032" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia rufescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis id="FDEFFB997693AC7A305E363DB18B7214" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it can be distinguished by its exserted style. For differences between this species and 
<taxonomicName id="372CDAEBC0C265A73896629B3FDD1908" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia lasiopoda" order="Myrtales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lasiopoda">
<emphasis id="AA5E9E861E8D040B5902151EF775630F" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Conostegia lasiopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see the discussion under the latter.
</paragraph>
<caption id="ED89A4FAFD7D84B73AD2BC087B6E9FC4" ID-Zenodo-Dep="973911" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure132" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96490" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" start="Figure 132" startId="F132">
